In #SOTU, Coloradans want @POTUS to reaffirm his commitment to the rule of law & respect for our institutions. 
Bruce S. from Denver says he wants to hear about “playing by the rules, and that no one, including the President, is above the law.” 9/x

In #SOTU, Coloradans want to hear that interference in our democracy will not be tolerated & we are taking steps to prevent such attacks from Russia—or others—in the future. 
Karl H. says he hopes addressing foreign interference in politics “wouldn’t be a partisan issue.” 8/x

In #SOTU, Coloradans want to hear commitment to protect #Dreamers & keep families together. 
Rita M. from Englewood wants to hear @POTUS address DACA. “We surely need to allow [#Dreamers] who were brought here from another country as children to become American citizens.” 7/x

In #SOTU, Coloradans want to hear plans to #ActOnClimate, like building resilient infrastructure, modernizing electricity grid & promoting bipartisan clean energy policies. 
Deana K. from CO Springs says “CO has no snow this year” & asks how admin will slow #climatechange. 6/x

In #SOTU, Coloradans want to know how we'll prepare our kids for 21st century economy. This means growing wages to keep up with the costs of housing, health care, and childcare. It means modernizing #highered & career & technical ed so students are ready for jobs of tomorrow. 5/x

Last October, @POTUS declared the #opioid epidemic a public health emergency, but hasn’t proposed new resources or funding to combat the growing problem. Tonight, we want to know precisely how he plans to work with communities to prioritize this crisis. #SOTU 4/x

In #SOTU, Coloradans want to hear concrete proposals to support our rural communities. From lowering health care costs to tackling the #opioidcrisis to investing in infrastructure, we need more than words. We need funding & action. #VoicesOfCO 3/x

In #SOTU, Coloradans want to hear @POTUS unite communities instead of continuing to divide us.
